  "Lead is stable at all temperatures": "",
  "U-238 (t₁/₂ = 4.47×10⁹ yr) decays to Pb-206. Measuring the U:Pb ratio gives the age of ancient rocks and minerals.": "",
  "The decay constant (λ) relates to half-life by:": "",
  "λ = t½ (decay constant equals the half-life)": "",
  "λ = 1/t½ (simple reciprocal of half-life)": "",
  "λ = ln2 / t₁/₂ (or t₁/₂ = 0.693/λ)": "",
  "λ = t½ × ln2 (half-life multiplied by 0.693)": "",
  "From the integrated rate law: N(t) = N₀e^(−λt). At t = t₁/₂: N = N₀/2. Solving: λ = ln(2)/t₁/₂ ≈ 0.693/t₁/₂.": "",
