  "5 minutes (6 half-lives: 600→9.4 remaining)": "",
  "10 minutes (3 half-lives: 600→300→150→75)": "",
  "600 → 75 = divide by 8 = 2³, so 3 half-lives. 30 min / 3 = 10 min half-life.": "",
  "The concept of 'secular equilibrium' in decay chains means:": "",
  "A long-lived parent reaches steady state with shorter-lived daughters (daughter activity equals parent activity)": "",
  "All isotopes in the decay chain have the same half-life and decay at exactly the same rate simultaneously": "",
  "All decay stops once the parent and daughter isotopes reach equal concentrations in the sample material": "",
  "Equilibrium is reached only when all radioactive material has fully decayed to stable daughter products": "",
  "Secular equilibrium: when a long-lived parent (slow decay) reaches steady state with short-lived daughters — activities become equal and daughter amounts remain constant.": "",
